29/07/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- On Monday (28 July), the OSCE Spillover Monitor Mission to Skopje announced the completion of a project to train 1,065 cadets drawn from the minority population to become part of Macedonia's multiethnic police force. 
The fifth and final graduation ceremony of the last 350 cadets in the programme will take place Wednesday. 
The project was completed with the help of the Macedonian Interior Ministry, in accordance with a commitment under the Ohrid Peace Accord to train and deploy 1,000 minority police officers by July 2003, a target that has now been surpassed. 
(MIA, OSCE Web site - 28/07/03)
